<body>
    <%- include('../navbar') %>
    <div class="content-fightinghunger">
        <div class="content-fightinghunger-header">
            <div class="content-fightinghunger-header-text">
                <p>We provide food assistance, </p><span>nutrition education, and support local farming for resilient food systems.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="content-fightinghunger-header-img">
                <img src="/img/hunger-bg.jpg">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="content-fightinghunger-container">
            <div class="content-fightinghunger-container-item">
                <div class="content-fightinghunger-container-item-text">
                    <strong>We work to build strong communities by supporting local farmers and improving access to food.</strong>
                    
                </div>
                <div class="content-fightinghunger-container-item-content">
<p>We work to build strong and sustainable communities by focusing on supporting local farmers and improving access to nutritious food. Our approach is rooted in the belief that everyone deserves food security and that empowering local agriculture can lead to long-term resilience. By providing resources and education to farmers, we help them adopt sustainable practices that increase productivity while protecting the environment. This, in turn, strengthens the local economy and reduces dependence on imported food sources. <br> <br>

    Improving access to food goes beyond just providing meals—it means ensuring that communities have reliable, affordable, and nutritious food available to them. We collaborate with community leaders, nutrition experts, and local organizations to identify and address specific needs within each community. Through initiatives like food banks, meal programs, and affordable farmers’ markets, we make healthy food options accessible to more people, particularly those in vulnerable or low-income areas. <br> <br>
    
    Additionally, we promote community education on nutrition and sustainable practices. Workshops, cooking classes, and informational sessions help residents learn about healthy eating and ways to maximize the nutritional value of their meals, even on a budget. By sharing knowledge about sustainable farming and nutritious food choices, we empower individuals to take an active role in their own well-being. <br> <br>
    
    Our work ultimately aims to build a cycle of support: as local farmers thrive, they can produce more and better-quality food for their communities, and as people gain access to nutritious food, they experience better health and a higher quality of life. Through these efforts, we are helping communities become more self-sufficient, resilient, and capable of facing future challenges.    </p>                </div>
                <div class="content-fightinghunger-container-item-img">
                    <img src="/img/img-ourwork-hunger.jpg" alt="Happy Farmer">
                </div>
            </div> 
            <div class="content-fightinghunger-container-item">
                <div class="content-fightinghunger-container-item-text">
                    <strong>Packaging food for the homeless, poor children, poor families of the HA organization.</strong>
                    
                </div>
                <div class="content-fightinghunger-container-item-content">
                    <p>The HA organization is dedicated to helping vulnerable groups by packaging and distributing food to the homeless, poor children, and low-income families. Volunteers work tirelessly to sort, pack, and deliver essential items, ensuring that those in need receive nutritious food to sustain themselves. By partnering with local food suppliers and donors, the organization maximizes its reach and impact, helping to ease the burden on struggling communities. The initiative not only addresses immediate hunger but also promotes hope and solidarity, showing that support is available for those facing hardships. Through its food assistance programs, HA aims to make a meaningful difference and inspire resilience among disadvantaged individuals and families.</p>
                    </div>
                <div class="content-fightinghunger-container-item-img">
                    <img src="/img/hunger-our.jpg" alt="HA organization">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
